(
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1C8D68FF57F893FE9A6A4B" box="[159,274,1866,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,899,921]" captionTargetBox="[183,1426,203,870]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[161,1426,193,878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Sertania gen. nov. species in dorsal and ventral views, respectively. 1 – 4, Sertania guttata comb. nov., male (DNA-voucher BLU 882) (1 – 2) from Capilla del Monte, Cordoba, Argentina (ZUEC), and female (3 – 4) from La Rioja, Argentina (MACN); 5 – 8, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov., male holotype (5 – 6) from Jaíba, Minas Gerais, Brazil (MNRJ), and female (DNA-voucher NS 0104) (7 – 8) from Sempre Vivas National Park, Buenópolis, Minas Gerais, Brazil (ZUEC); 9 – 12, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov., male (DNA-voucher BLU 889) (9 – 10) from Custódia, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), and female (11 – 12) from Catimbau National Park, Pernambuco, Brazil (Cemafauna-Univasf). Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892879/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
