<subSubSection id="C31F78D00C1D8D69FF5FFF4EFC4E6F30" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBA2B5B0C1D8D69FF5FFF4EFC4E6F30" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FF5FFF4EFE996D98" bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length: males 
<quantity id="4CFD86BE0C1D8D69FDE0FF41FD296D87" box="[552,673,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 mm</quantity>
(n = 3), females 
<quantity id="4CFD86BE0C1D8D69FCA9FF41FC526D87" box="[865,986,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 mm</quantity>
(n = 2). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FBF4FF41FA856D98" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="P. Jauffret, J. Jauffret &amp; Pessoa" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1084,1293,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lambedor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FBF4FF41FA856D98" box="[1084,1293,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Sertania lambedor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2424A320C1D8D69FADCFF4EFE896DFD" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FADCFF4EFE896DFD" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">comb. nov., stat nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is more similar and closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FD28FF65FCEE6DFC" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[736,870,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FD28FF65FCEE6DFC" box="[736,870,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, differences in the 
<collectionCode id="ED14B39E0C1D8D69FB02FF65FA8F6DFC" box="[1226,1287,188,212]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">DNA</collectionCode>
barcode are appreciable (2.67%, 
<tableCitation id="C6871EE00C1D8D69FE48FF06FE5C6DD0" box="[384,468,223,248]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,239,691,714]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison of inter- and intraspecific divergences (%) for the DNA “ barcodes ” of Sertania gen. nov. species (number of individuals in parentheses). Values of divergence above 2 percent are in bold; (--) does not apply." pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Table 2</tableCitation>
) and adults can be easily distinguished from the latter by the bright yellow coloration in males and females (
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1D8D69FE59FEDDFD846C34" box="[401,524,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,899,921]" captionTargetBox="[183,1426,203,870]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[161,1426,193,878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Sertania gen. nov. species in dorsal and ventral views, respectively. 1 – 4, Sertania guttata comb. nov., male (DNA-voucher BLU 882) (1 – 2) from Capilla del Monte, Cordoba, Argentina (ZUEC), and female (3 – 4) from La Rioja, Argentina (MACN); 5 – 8, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov., male holotype (5 – 6) from Jaíba, Minas Gerais, Brazil (MNRJ), and female (DNA-voucher NS 0104) (7 – 8) from Sempre Vivas National Park, Buenópolis, Minas Gerais, Brazil (ZUEC); 9 – 12, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov., male (DNA-voucher BLU 889) (9 – 10) from Custódia, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), and female (11 – 12) from Catimbau National Park, Pernambuco, Brazil (Cemafauna-Univasf). Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892879/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Figs. 9–12</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FDD7FEDDFCB06C34" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[543,824,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="guttata" subSpecies="jaibensis">
Furthermore, 
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FD71FEDDFCB06C34" box="[697,824,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents an infusion of red-orange scaling on the male dorsal surface and light yellow scaling on the female. The ventral FW discal area of the male is brick red and the HW discal area lighter white with reddish scaling, and the post-medial area darker with black scaling. The submarginal row of brown spots is more apparent. The female ventral surface has light orange ground color on the FW and darker orange infused with white scaling on HW. Margin of uncus straight in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FBA0FE4DFB676C84" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="P. Jauffret, J. Jauffret &amp; Pessoa" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1128,1263,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lambedor">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FBA0FE4DFB676C84" box="[1128,1263,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. lambedor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1D8D69FAC8FE4DFADC6C85" box="[1280,1364,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[171,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Male genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 19 – 22, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina (ZUEC), lateral view (19), tegumen and uncus in dorsal view (20), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (21), valvae in lateral view (22). 23 – 24, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. paratype from Diamantina, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUP), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (23), valvae in lateral view (24). 25 – 26, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (25), valvae in lateral view (26). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892883/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FA4FFE4DFF6E6CF8" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FA4FFE4DFF6E6CF8" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FEEDFE61FE226CF8" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[293,426,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FEEDFE61FE226CF8" box="[293,426,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the margin of uncus present a dorsal projection (
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1D8D69FC3EFE6EFB096CF8" box="[1014,1153,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[171,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Male genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 19 – 22, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina (ZUEC), lateral view (19), tegumen and uncus in dorsal view (20), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (21), valvae in lateral view (22). 23 – 24, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. paratype from Diamantina, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUP), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (23), valvae in lateral view (24). 25 – 26, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (25), valvae in lateral view (26). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892883/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Figs 21, 23</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FA4FFE61FF736CDC" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FA4FFE61FF736CDC" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
present ostium bursae with oval opening and pointed signa (
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1D8D69FC03FE05FBDA6CDC" box="[971,1106,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 32" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[176,1425,373,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,373,1516]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 32. Female genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 27, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Pichinal, Salta, Argentina (CJC), ventral view. 28 – 30, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. from Buenópolis, Minas Gerais, Brazil (ZUEC), papilla analis (28), sterigma in ventral view (29), note the oval opening (arrow), signus (30). 31 – 32, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), sterigma in ventral view (31), note the circular opening (arrow), signus (32). Scale bars = 0.5 mm (Fig. 27) and 0.1 mm (Figs 28 – 32)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892885/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Figs 29–30</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1D8D69FB7BFE05FAB66CDC" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="P. Jauffret, J. Jauffret &amp; Pessoa" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1203,1342,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lambedor">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1D8D69FB7BFE05FAB66CDC" box="[1203,1342,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">S. lambedor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the ostium bursae with circular opening and less pointed signa (
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1D8D69FCFEFE26FC316F30" box="[822,953,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 32" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[176,1425,373,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,373,1516]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 32. Female genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 27, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Pichinal, Salta, Argentina (CJC), ventral view. 28 – 30, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. from Buenópolis, Minas Gerais, Brazil (ZUEC), papilla analis (28), sterigma in ventral view (29), note the oval opening (arrow), signus (30). 31 – 32, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), sterigma in ventral view (31), note the circular opening (arrow), signus (32). Scale bars = 0.5 mm (Fig. 27) and 0.1 mm (Figs 28 – 32)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892885/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="174">Figs 31–32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
